1
00:00:00,230 --> 00:00:06,230
In this video we are going to compare vertical slice architecture versus clean architecture.

2
00:00:06,770 --> 00:00:12,860
Vertical slice architecture emphasizes organizing software development around the features, cutting

3
00:00:12,860 --> 00:00:15,290
through all layers in a vertical manner.

4
00:00:15,290 --> 00:00:19,400
Each feature or slice is developed and deployed independently.

5
00:00:20,140 --> 00:00:26,320
On the other hand, clean architecture focuses on separation of concerns and dependency rules.

6
00:00:26,350 --> 00:00:33,280
It organizes the code into layers with the most stable and business agnostic layers at the center of

7
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:40,000
the entities, and use cases and external concerns like UI and data access layers on the outer layers.

8
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:43,090
With vertical slice architecture.

9
00:00:43,090 --> 00:00:49,720
Development teams concentrate on delivering complete features, each potentially touching all layers

10
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:50,620
of the stack.

11
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:58,030
It is closely aligned with the agile methodologies where delivering working, testable features rapidly

12
00:00:58,030 --> 00:01:05,920
is a key, but the clean architecture advocates for a more structured approach, ensuring that business

13
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,920
logic is decoupled from the external concerns.

14
00:01:08,950 --> 00:01:14,380
This approach is beneficial for long terme maintainability and scalability.

15
00:01:15,410 --> 00:01:22,340
Vertical slice architecture shines in scenarios where the rapid development and delivery of the independent

16
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:23,870
features are critical.

17
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:31,640
It is well suited for agile teams working on complex applications with numerous features that may change

18
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:33,350
or evolve independently.

19
00:01:34,270 --> 00:01:41,050
Clean architecture is ideal for large scale applications where long Tum maintenance and scalability

20
00:01:41,050 --> 00:01:46,990
and the ability to adapt to changing business requirements or technologies are paramount.

21
00:01:47,020 --> 00:01:53,380
It ensures that core business logic remains unaffected by changes in the external layers.

22
00:01:54,530 --> 00:02:01,370
So once you choose vertical slice over the clean architecture, the first reason is rapid development

23
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:02,450
and deployment.

24
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:09,410
When the priority is to develop and deploy features rapidly and independently, vertical slice is more

25
00:02:09,410 --> 00:02:10,220
appropriate.

26
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:13,820
The second reason is agile and scrum teams.

27
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:20,690
For teams practicing the agile or scrum that need to deliver complete features in short cycles.

28
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:24,140
Vertical Slice aligns well with these methodologies.

29
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:27,670
And another reason is microservices.

30
00:02:27,670 --> 00:02:34,150
In a microservice architecture, where each service is often responsible for a distinct feature or business

31
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:34,900
capability.

32
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:37,960
Vertical slice can be particularly effective.

33
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:46,180
So let's see our issue of microservices and compare with the catalog versus organic microservices catalog

34
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:49,030
microservices using the vertical slice architecture.

35
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:55,870
So in our issue of microservices, the catalog microservices manage the products categories and inventory.

36
00:02:55,870 --> 00:02:59,110
And it is using the vertical slice architecture.

37
00:02:59,230 --> 00:03:06,250
Each feature, like adding any product or updating inventory or managing categories, is developed as

38
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,420
a separate slice.

39
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:15,040
Each slice would include its own API endpoint, business logic and data access code, allowing for the

40
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:21,370
rapid development and updates to individual aspects of the product catalog without affecting the others.

41
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:26,180
Mặt khác, ordering microservices sử dụng clean architecture.

42
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:32,180
Vậy ordering microservices xử lý logic xử lý đơn hàng, bao gồm quản lý giỏ hàng, đặt hàng

43
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:34,190
và xử lý thanh toán.

44
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:41,120
Với clean architecture, các quy tắc kinh doanh cốt lõi và các trường hợp sử dụng của xử lý đơn hàng là trung tâm và

45
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:45,680
được cách ly khỏi các mối quan tâm bên ngoài như các hoạt động cơ sở dữ liệu hoặc UI.

46
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:53,000
Sự tách biệt này đảm bảo rằng các quy tắc kinh doanh quan trọng vẫn ổn định và không bị ảnh hưởng bởi các thay đổi trong các hệ thống bên ngoài,

47
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,480
như cổng thanh toán hoặc schema cơ sở dữ liệu.

48
00:03:56,990 --> 00:04:02,870
Vậy lựa chọn giữa vertical slice architecture và clean architecture phụ thuộc vào các yêu cầu cụ thể

49
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:04,400
của dự án.

50
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:11,270
Vertical slice tập trung hơn vào tính năng và nhanh nhẹn, và nó lý tưởng cho phát triển tính năng nhanh chóng và

51
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:12,170
triển khai.

52
00:04:12,530 --> 00:04:18,980
Clean architecture phù hợp hơn cho các ứng dụng quy mô lớn, tồn tại lâu dài, nơi các quy tắc kinh doanh

53
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:22,250
phải được cách ly khỏi các thay đổi bên ngoài.

54
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:28,970
Chúng ta sẽ sử dụng cả hai kiến trúc trong các microservices khác nhau có thể tận dụng các điểm mạnh của chúng theo

55
00:04:28,970 --> 00:04:31,250
yêu cầu của từng microservice.

